Prepare recovery plans for:
Server failure
Database corruption
Data center outage
Accidental data deletion
Concepts:
RPO (Recovery Point Objective)
RTO (Recovery Time Objective)




Disaster Recovery Scenarios
Server Failure Plan: Restoring operations on new hardware or a standby node by deploying backups or initiating an automatic failover sequence.

Database Corruption Plan: Running integrity checks to isolate damage, then repairing the files or restoring clean backups up to the point of failure.

Data Center Outage Plan: Routing application traffic to a geographically distant secondary site where database replicas are hosted and ready for activation.

Accidental Data Deletion Plan: Recovering lost records by using point-in-time log restorations, backup side-loads, or database snapshot rollbacks.

Key Metrics
RPO (Recovery Point Objective): The maximum duration of acceptable data loss measured in time, defining how frequently you must take backups.

RTO (Recovery Time Objective): The maximum targeted duration of downtime allowed to completely restore database availability and bring systems online.

